article.headline: Austin Peay 69, E. Illinois 54
article.story: CLARKSVILLE, Tenn. -- Drake Reed scored 28 points and Austin Peay defeated Eastern Illinois 69-54 on Thursday night. Austin Peay (16-12, 12-5 Ohio Valley Conference) forced 15 Panthers' turnovers and won the rebounding battle 31-27. The Governors extended their lead to as many as 17, 69-52 when Wes Channels hit a free throw with 1:45 left in the game. Anthony Campbell added 11 points for Austin Peay, which also won the earlier meeting between the two teams, 81-73 on Dec. 6. Eastern Illinois (12-16, 8-9) was paced by Romain Martin with 14 points and T.J. Marion with 13. The Panthers shot just 10 percent form 3-point range (1 of 10), while the Governors were 6-for-13 (46.2 percent).
